			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=15715'>







<img src="/eq/i/icons/Classes/warrior.gif" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=1628#M1628">51</a> of 71
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 427 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Iustus_TM wrote:<BR><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Frodlin wrote:<BR>
<DIV>I'm going to ask you the same thing I ask everyone who claims that hybrids are faring poorly at the moment:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Exactly which mobs can you not tank because of your class?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Include:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Single group mobs</DIV>
<DIV>Offtank Mobs</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>It is not about what you <STRONG>cannot</STRONG> tank. It is possible for a wizard to main tank rallos zek in time. You can do it. Of course, it might take 25 clerics and 50 tries, but it <STRONG>can</STRONG> be done.</P>
<P>The same is true about any of the challenging single group mobs and offtank mobs. Whether you are talking about any of the muramite names in kodtaz (non-animals), or offtanking in uqua, or in ikkinz, or in tacvi, it is all the same. Mobs are much much much easier to tank or offtank with a warrior. In every single one of these cases the healing requirements are significantly less, less healers needed, less mana expended.</P>
<P>Using utility to balance inferior tanks just doesnt work well. The job of being a tank is too specific, you either do it well, or you dont. </P>
<P>I will say it again. I dont want to take over the warriors role of tanking. I want to share it. I was a tank when I started this game 5 years ago, and I want to be one today. Expansion by expansion warriors have been taking more and more of the tank role, until today they dominate all aspects. I do not think this make sense. </P>
<P>Does it make sense that the ideal raid has 8-10 warriors and say, 2 knights? Is that how it should be? Does it make sense that if you have 8-10 knights and only 2 warriors, there are many raids you just wont be able to do, because not enough warriors? Really?</P>
<P>I do not want to be better than warriors. I just want to have a job that I am good at, that is valuble and desired. I am perfectly happy if warriors are equally valued for the same job. I just dont want to hear every time we are doing new content, "Oh, we need a warrior to tank that", or "Ok, lets get warriors on all these adds", and so on. </P>
<P>As it is right now, its near impossible for the game developers to design even a raid that has adds that are supposed to be tanked by either a warrior or a knight. They always come off being either too easy for warriors, or impossible for knights.</P>
<P>-I</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Iustus,</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Are you seriously telling me that you have no role in Uqua?&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Not only can you tank trap mobs, and statics, but few spells in Uqua are cast more often than waves (Paladin group heals).&nbsp;&nbsp; Nor has anyone EVER sent me a tell informing me that they have spirit touch.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Uqua is about as balanced as it can get.&nbsp; Warriors&nbsp;survive trap mobs more reliably, yet they're doable by knights, and knights would do them by default because of their dramatic&nbsp;ranged aggro advantage if there weren't a delineation.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Every wipe I've ever seen in Uqua has never been the result of a knight tank dying, but the result of a healer getting toasted because of heal aggro while standing in the midst of the casters.&nbsp; We actually use knight pre-aggro in Uqua with a handoff, it's turned out to be WAY safer than using incite/bellow.&nbsp; Uqua is also a great "pull team" zone, where SK's really shine (low level pet pulling in particular).&nbsp; There are different incentives to use different tanks, and different roles for the 3 classes.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>No one offtanks trash in Ikkinz, because all the mobs are mezzable, we use a Paladin MA&nbsp;in Ikkinz, forget offtanking, &nbsp;but on some encounters warriors are stronger (Glorification splits, Firedudes), and on other encounters Paladins are stronger (Altar Overseer, Righteousness, KotA Adds).&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Single group named Muramites&nbsp;in KodTaz are easier tanked by warriors *as they should be*, but they're NOT impossible by knights, or even that much more difficult with knights.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The "You can tank Rallos with a wizard and 25 clerics, and this is the same as Paladins" hyperbolae is amazing to me.&nbsp;&nbsp; In just about every case, a small change in group makeup can pretty much ensure success.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As you're quite aware, I don't buy the whole "We should be equal tanks balanced by utility" argument, because not only do warriors currently have no utility, but because the amount of utility we would need to come up to your level would change my class completely.&nbsp;&nbsp; The little list you offerred would be what I'd refer to as "a small start".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<img src="http://i12.photobucket.com/albums/a247/Ridefort/frodsig.gif" height=110 width=300><br><br>Warrior Class Correspondent<br>"54 random people is no more a raid than a heap of building materials is a house"
							</div>
								
