		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<DIV>I think about it, and Warriors are as people have said the measureing stick for wich all other classes are to be judged and rated against. If thats so, adding utility would detract from the purity of the warrior class and result in skewed results when you compare things. Wich would lead to even more horrible class balancing, more problems, more nerfs, more whineing. </DIV></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>And yes the list of Utility that can be added to warriors is very small wich would not compensate for what is "being taken"</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I do not whole heartedly like or agree with the following, but I do agree it might make things more right in the game.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Move Knights to DI 1-19 like warriors. But give warriors an innate shielding mod(like the augs and %shielding mod items)&nbsp;that scales as they level. If you gave warriors 1-18 instead for the DI, the change would be far to dramatic and trivialize things, and we would end up right back where we are now.</DIV>
<DIV>SK's.... Remove Sk Spell casting subtelty, give them an innate toggle switch that they can turn on to increase their agro or decrease it. If they are supposed to be masters of hate something like this would make sense. It could use endurance to have it on, neutral or negative agro. It would be like giving sk's an innate VoT they can click off if they dont need to generate extra agro.&nbsp; Being able to turn it into an agro decreaser for themselves means you dont promote them having to attempt to Feign every 12seconds.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The sad truth is;</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>There are people who cry becasue they are&nbsp;NOT the MT, not wether or not their class, their skill, or if they have the&nbsp;ability and gear to tank it or not. </DIV>
<DIV>They would cry if someone else of their class, equally geared or worse geared ended up being MT for something.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>Alot of that has to do with who you are grouped/raiding with and their personal prefrences. </DIV>
<DIV>There is no way to win.</DIV></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
