		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Since being in a raid guild for the last 9 months I have been too busy worrying about adds and protecting the casters to even think about MTing. I have been MA a few times depending on what they have going, Yes&nbsp;I have even MTed some pretty big fella's...Still, I'm more useful as a sentinal guarding the rear or flank simply because of my range agro, I can target a mob from 200 feet and zing, have it run passed all the healers straight to me.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I do sometimes wish&nbsp;I had some better survivalbility in certain area's but I'm generally pretty happy with the situation as it is now. The guild is currantly Txevu, MPG trials. Perhaps higher geared knights think differently. I can tank pretty much any single group situation thus far even DoD hard missions.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>How to make the three tanks equally desireable, hmmm, Most SK spells are either for agro or for self healing, they tend to be very selfish, even fd is a selfish, it's a "I'm going to live and you aint" spell. While it is true that it's utility, it's mostly self suffcient utility. Partly why we make good offtanks, we can stay alive with just shamans healing in some cases.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;However,&nbsp;I have few spells that can help groups or raids as a whole, so my group utility is low, most of it is my self utility being used to a groups advantage. That's more a matter of smart tactics rather &nbsp;than class design.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I think we all have to realize that we are all tanks, my job is agro and tanking, it isn't healing, it isn't buffing, slowing, debuffing, isn't even pulling much anymore. My CC control is all about agroing mobs. You will note that&nbsp;I didn't say MTing, simply tanking. I agro things that we don't want hitting other classes,&nbsp;thats what I do. If the mobs kill me instead of the healer and we win, then I did my job, I'm the expendable trooper. (&nbsp;I would prolly like that they didn't kill me quit so easily)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Yes, I am the agrowhore for the warriors who take mobs off me, so? My job isn't neccasarily to fight that mob till it's dead, it's to look for more adds. I have been in fights where&nbsp;I have agroed nearly every inc mob and handed off to a warrior, it makes fights run more smoothly.&nbsp;So what if I mostly play interferance for warriors?&nbsp;I have been given free reign on raids to agro anything&nbsp;I think warrents it, so I must be doing something right.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
