<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Robobobo wrote:<BR>
<DIV>I don't mean to flame, you sound like a warrior, but you sound like a warrior who's completely given up on any idea of a definitive role in the game. You're basically offering the hybrids every advantage we have over them and not removing the myriad of advantages they already have over us via their spell books. Warrior should be a superior tank - having content in game that requires the supreme tank is not unrealistic imo. There are plenty of RL examples of where supreme warriors are needed to accomplish a given goal, and where an army fails without the best of the best. There are also myriad fantasy situations where this fits in. I would gladly give up a certain amount of dps in order to retain this goal with which I created my character, but if you want to upgrade the mitigation of hybrids, there should be an equal mitigation upgrade to warriors. The recent upgrade to hybrids by removing the usefullness of warriors in the situations mentioned is imo aggregiously misappropriated, including the fact that this merely opened the doorway to charmed npc tanking. Bring more roleplay back into the game -- don't carbon copy the warrior role into the hybrid role and completely nullify the role of the supreme tank. The hybrids consider this arrogant of course, they think that we are coveting the tank role at all costs, but in reality we chose a class that is entirely a tank class, while they chose a class that is possibly primarily a tank class, and in entirely imaginably secondarily a tank class.</DIV><BR>
