		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Sortof the wrong thread.<br><br>The actual number is something like ~386 innate HP advantage after self buffs (like AoTC) are applied. However, some Knight buffs were improved and Warriors received the Sturdiness AA ability (500 more HP's when they have it all) and "-1 DI".<br><br>Don't be too impressed one way or another about maximum HP's. Provided a mob can't kill you outright in a single round an SK's lifetaps or a Paladin's heal spells and procs can prop them up quite a bit - enough that they can solo mobs Warriors must group.<br><br>Warriors ARE (so far) unmatched at surviving the most brutal battles - but read that as RAID boss mob battles. There are no groupable mobs I'm aware of that Knights can not tank. Still if you want to be a raid MT, roll a Warrior.<br><br>If instead you want very adequate tanking vs. all single group content, a crucial tanking role and other roles in raids, very attractive secondary abilities, and much better soloing capabilitythan a Warrior, then roll a Knight.<br><br>IMO SK's are a great choice for players that want a lot of offensive related flexability. They can pull quite effectively, get past mobs that can't see invis (for goodness sakes get a CoS - it's a must item IMO), have great aggro, and can be very tough while dishing out good damage.<br><br>Alternately, Paladins do have in effect a pocket Cleric. Part Warrior/part Cleric is a powerful combination. If I got their 90% res everytime I've died I'd probably have another 100 AA's or so. They've got great buffs, particularly in combination with a Druid or Shaman group main healer, their healing ability in post level 66 group content isn't bad at all, and to be honest in stunable content their stuns are waaaaay overpowered.<br><br>If I wasn't a hardcore raider and wasn't determined to MT, I would be playing a Knight. I have recently taken my Paladin out of mothballs, because frankly when not raiding the Paladin class is a LOT more fun to play than a Warrior.<br><br>IMO if you aren't determined to be a hardcore raiding MT, roll a Knight. You'll have fun on raids and a lot of fun while grouping and soloing.<p>Message Edited by Battleblade-Xegony on <span class=date_text>12-13-2005</span> <span class=time_text>08:29 PM</span>	
