		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			A huge problem that I can see is the increasing difficulty for casual players who are not already 70 to get gear.   The population on several servers (I play semi-actively on 4 servers) has moved into DoN and DoD content.   For a lower-60s warrior, there are few groups available to help with collecting gear (BoT has had 1 person in it (me) the last 5 times I've zoned in there -- no new tanks are actively collecting Planes armor).  And almost all casual-60 characters are unable to tank in the DoN/DoD zones because their gear is not up to the task.<br><br>I can see how this problem might become more significant in the future.  It's not just the casual/raid arguement, but the player base moves to the newer content.  The 70th level characters are reluctant to want a 67-69th tank in the group for 'current' content, because those characters might not be able to handle that content.<br><br>The tanking classes are so dependant on their gear, that newer players are going to be hard pressed to keep up, and replace the ranks of players that retire.   Alts can be twinked, new raiders can get guild-twinked, but the casual player is really going to have a tough time.  I may soon be forced to concentrate on a single character.	
		</td></tr>
