		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Try making friends and exploring the game instead of jumping directly on the latest expansion band wagon.  You might not find the game so hard then.  Try sebilis, try veksar, try castle in disease.  Maybe give normal zones in dod a try, same with so many other zones I wont list here.  You got 90 percent of explored content out there, make a few friends and explore it.  Find out where chardok b is, and sol c.  Go check out temple of veeshan for some fun.  Look up quests like the one for 100 hp shoulders that requires drops from 4 zones barely anybody ever goes to anymore.  So much stuff to do to build up your toon to handle later content, and I bet you are  like a majority of casual EQ and ignore it.  This game is very doable, progress wise, when you got a few friends.  Oh well, stopping here on this response.<br><br>As for the rest of the thread<br><br>These same old arguements get old over time.  Everybody's problems are that so and so class can do what they do, but nobody bothers to mention the insane gear that so and so class requires to do so.  So what if a anguish geared shaman can tank circles around casual tanks, there arent that many anguish geared shamans that will be hanging out where those casual tanks hang.  So what if a anguish druid shows up a casual cleric when it comes to flashiness of healing, nuking, and being all around useful to a group, that druid is heads and tails above the cleric gear and most likely aa wise.  What it all comes down to is the game becomes blurred after people start getting insane raid items, and people start clearing 800 aa.  Everybody's problems are with people who are far better geared and aa'd.  <br><br>Warriors complain about knights, but a casual knight and casual warrior are still balanced in every way but aggro.  Casual's try somethign hard, the knights will likely be massacred, while the warrior under defensive will be triumphant.  Most of you here are guilty of this one thing, when you say a knight replacing a warrior, you never mention specific gear lv and aa lv.  A normal knight wont out tank a normal warrior on the DoD spell missions.  A hardcore casual knight who has full cultural and 700 aa's might out tank a normal warrior with a mix of baz gear, 1 piece of cultural, and 200aa but that person has alot more investment in his toon.  None of your arguements are worth anything because you never give specifics.  You argue for the moon, but you compare apples and oranges doing so.  <br><br>Who cares if somebody with 400 days played on his toon out shines a person with 20 days.  Who cares if a knight who has raided 5 years out does a casual or normal warrior.  The point is, the only time one class out does another class who has a specialist job, is when the first class is a good deal better geared and a whole lot better aa'd than the specialist class.  Knights can out tank warrior, if we have much higher quality loot and that warrior doesnt have all thier defensive aa's and the knight does.  A raid warrior can make 5 casual, and even mid lv raid geared, knights look like wet paper sacks with how tough they are.  <br><br>That is basically the whole point of this situation.  Nobody can ever compare exactly the same things between classes because there are always variables.  There are raiders with 200 aa, and casual with 700 aa.  Unless those raiders are way better geared than the casual with 700 aa, that casual with 700 aa will likely show up the 200 aa toon due to development of their toon.<br><br>There are way too many variables, so there can never be a truly fair comparison of classes.  There is balance in this game if you quit comparing people from different stations in eq life.  The only problem is, as a person gets raid geared and their aa get high, the balance begins to blur, and the game opens up to raiders in a whole new way that cant really be compared.  <br><br>Sigh, cant believe I typed this on christmas, but what the heck.<br><br>Anyway, merry christmas.<p>Message 