		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Not a bad post Bruennor, if a little Paladin centric.<br><br>From a Warrior centric viewpoint, let me say:<br><br>Don't for a minute complain as a Paladin group content is too hard. I brought a 52 Paladin out of retirement, geared him up, and brought him to level 66 because I'm convinced that group content isn't too hard and Defensive means VERY little when the difference between named mobs and normal yard trash is negligable.<br><br>IMO a Knight is much more enjoyable to play in single group content than a Warrior. But such things are a matter of personal preference.<br><br>Is the path toward a capable Paladin easy peasy compared to a Warrior? Not at all. Most of the spells are in fact pretty weak with the exception of stuns until you reach your 60's. You still need to gear up to be a tank - that's what a tank is, AC and HP's. If you can't make the effort to acquire those, roll a halfling Druid.<br><br>Bruennor is absolutely right about one thing and it can't be stressed enough. In EQ 2 can do more than 1, 6 more than 2, and 50 more than 6. If you want to solo or hang out exclulsively with the three friends you have in RL from your neighborhood, go play Doom. If you are absolutely determined to go it alone, then roll a soloing class and don't utter a word of complaint when you get to level 70 and others who are more social exceed you.	
