<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=13141#M13141">70</a> of 71
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 94 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<br><blockquote><hr>BruennorB wrote:<br>Try making friends and exploring the game instead of jumping directly on the latest expansion band wagon.  You might not find the game so hard then.  Try sebilis, try veksar, try castle in disease.  Maybe give normal zones in dod a try, same with so many other zones I wont list here.  You got 90 percent of explored content out there, make a few friends and explore it.  Find out where chardok b is, and sol c.  Go check out temple of veeshan for some fun.  Look up quests like the one for 100 hp shoulders that requires drops from 4 zones barely anybody ever goes to anymore.  So much stuff to do to build up your toon to handle later content, and I bet you are  like a majority of casual EQ and ignore it.  This game is very doable, progress wise, when you got a few friends.  Oh well, stopping here on this response.<br></blockquote><br><br><br>While I appreciate your input here, BruennorB, it isn't quite as easy as you make it sound.  Players simply aren't using the older content like they used to.  Building a group to go to Veksar, or PoDisease, or Caverns of Exhile, or even newer places like Harbinger's Spire can easily take well over an hour.  When you only have 3 hours to play, that's a huge overhead and a deterrent.  Most players aren't going to devote that much time to group building.<br><br>Look into BoT or Storms on your server.  Unless there's a raid there, you'll probably find yourself alone.  With the number of alternative zones where a player can get experience, the player base is moving from the older content to newer, easier experience.  The old content provides tank classes the gear necessary to function in the newer zones.  Classes that aren't as equipment-focused as melee classes don't have the same pressures.  When a wizard can function in Wall of Slaughter at 55, and a 55th tank can't unless they are phenomenally geared or just soaking with someone else tanking.<br><br>A group of friends isn't going to resolve this problem.  Any group of level 55s is going to have 2-3 capable of functioning in WoS groups in support roles.  This puts internal pressure on the group.   I have a cleric alt that I play with a regular group.  The tanks there are 2 paladins, who are more 'undergeared' than my warrior.  It's difficult wanting to go to some place, only to have the tanks unable to perform their expected role in the group.  My warrior plays regularly with several friends, but still doesn't have the gear needed to go to places the others would like.  The tank (and their gear and AAs) is the biggest determining factor on what content the group can explore.<br><br>Other than this slight difference of perspective, I would agree with everything you said BreunnerB.  Very well stated.	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
