	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=80701'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<span style='color:#CC6600;'>JazzyJoyce</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Master<br>
			
				Posts: 719<br>
				
				Registered: 11-17-2004
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=80701'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=13144#M13144">71</a> of 71
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 87 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		
				background-color: #050A0E; 
				
				 background-image: none;
				 
				background-repeat: repeat-x;
				" 
			>
			<DIV>Bah, that's typical responce's, and although true, impractical. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Let's face it, all that old content out there is more then less, not worth the trouble. You can get a group to go anywhere, but it's not going to last very long. Experience sucks, drops are too low, what drops was only good for YOUR main 10 levels ago. Etc. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Yet when someone ask's advice about something like this, always someone who done the old content when the old content was worth something say's "You should go to A zone with some friends". The trouble with that is exactly what Mendel just said. Certain class's will be ok with it, but the Healer's and utility class's can get good groups in much better content, with higher drops, without needing the gear to be there. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>"Think your snare will work on level 65's?"&nbsp; "Probably" "Come on over to Left wall then!" or "We need a healer, can you come?" to a level 55 cleric for WOS. "Can you track?" "Sure" "Join please" </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>All that is NORMAL when I get on anything other then my warrior. My warrior get's asked:&nbsp;"How much HP/AC do you have?" and my responce is what determines if they want me or not. If I don't have X amount in HP I won't be consider'd. X amount can be 10k to 12k, depending on what the group thinks should be able to do that type of content. If your not level 70, you probably won't get asked for anything over NC level. NO creator's or even WOS, since ussually they will ask a level 70 for either of them first. Which bring's back the reason to do the OLDER CONTENT. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Ok, now that I got that out of my system, I'll try to help with the actual problem, which is finding a group for the older zone's.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I can only give you an example of what I do. I have a few friends that will go anywhere I want to go. I can go to any open POP Zone with a (High level) shammy or druid, and be just fine. If you can find at least one of the healer class's, then all you need is extra's for dps. You can use anyone you want for this, and what I do is look for people in the guild first, who I think the experience might be worth it to them. I have been known to take level 47+&nbsp;people to WOS (as an example), or level 55 people to POV, etc. BOT needs flag or level 62, so just try and get someone level 62 that would find it interesting. Another thing to note, Cleric's get Cheal at level 39, so you can use a level 47 cleric to heal, if your able to tank the content easily.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Bassically, as a Tank, you can use many different level's of people to group with you, at lower level's. So if your level 55 for example, grab some people around level 39+ to come aid you. Pick content that won't smash them, but that will give you experience. You make good friends this way, and they will practically follow you anywhere (if they are truely wanting to help). You will be able to tell who come's to group as a friend, and who come's just for the free ride. Ussually, it will be the one's screaming for every single drop that won't be worth your time later. You just learn which one's to grab when you set off on your daily grinds. You build a good ring of friends around you, by offering different place's to go to, as well as upgrades for people that can actually use them, and your staying ahead of them in level to be able to take them to tougher and better place's of experience untill your bassically where you want to be.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I personally took&nbsp;groups to SoL A, SoL B, Velk's Labyrinth, Old Sebilis, The Hole, Dranik Scar, POJ Basement, Grieg's End (Servitor of Luclin), POI, UP (Rumblecrush, Zelnathak, etc.), POV, Lavaspinner's Lair, Stillmoon Temple, &nbsp;BOT, NC, WOS, etc. Depending on what their level's are and what level I was at the time. Most of the time, almost training the group, or groups of player's till they are of level to progress in content that actually give's me some good experience as well. It takes time, patience, and even having to teach them things to be able to do stuff that is challenging to you. It also builds some loyalty base for you.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If your looking to get into the high game, I would suggest a totally different approach though. I would suggest you find a guild that is doing POP, and try to join/help them on their raids. Sooner or later, especially if your truly there to help them, they will ask you to join, or ask you to apply their guild. After getting in that guild, do your best to upgrade as much as possible untill that guild get's to a stopping point or barrier that they are unable to pass (Not something they just fail, but a real stop, like a couple month's go by and still no farther). At this point I would look into what other guilds are requiring, and try to get into one that&nbsp; is doing something like GOD, or OOW. If you get into a guild like that, you may or may not have to change guild's again. This is the fastest way I know of, on how to progress.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I have a friend that changed guild's about 5 times, and is now in the number one guild on my server. He was a person that was way behind me when we first met, and is now way above me (One of the best monks in the game). He finally found a guild that raids exactly to his liking, and has been in it for around a year or more now. He did it by bassically going from guild to guild, till he had all the prerequisits to get in the guild he is now. I believe anyone could do it this way, even a Warrior. Just something else for you to look into.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							"One falsehood destroys a thousand truths." "Do not think of yourself higher than you ought to think" "If you are not guilty of the robbery then you should not hold on to the loot!" -NOEL BRYSON, Ph

The wise discuss ideas, the normal discuss events, the ignorant discuss other's.
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
